        <h1>Requirements for Professionals</h1>
        <p>
            The SAAHAS platform aims to connect victims of domestic violence with certified and qualified professionals. 
            Here are the requirements for counselors, legal advisors, and doctors who wish to join our platform:
        </p>

        <section>
            <h2>Counselors</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Must hold a valid degree in psychology, counseling, or a related field.</li>
                <li>Minimum of 3 years of experience in counseling, especially dealing with domestic violence cases.</li>
                <li>Ability to provide both in-person and virtual consultations.</li>
                <li>Submit proof of certifications and licenses during the registration process.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Legal Advisors</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Must be a licensed attorney with specialization in family law or related areas.</li>
                <li>At least 2 years of experience in handling cases involving domestic violence.</li>
                <li>Ability to provide legal advice through the platform and assist victims in filing cases.</li>
                <li>Submit necessary documentation and proof of bar membership.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Doctors</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Must have a valid medical degree and be licensed to practice in their region.</li>
                <li>Experience in dealing with trauma cases or injuries resulting from domestic violence.</li>
                <li>Provide medical consultations online and, if needed, in person.</li>
                <li>Submit certificates and proof of medical registration during onboarding.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <p>
            If you meet the above requirements and are passionate about making a difference, 
            we invite you to <a href="/signup">join the SAAHAS platform</a>.
        </p>
